snippet.textDisplay: PEOPLE:  Start trying your best wherever you live to get on the internet and buy flour and bulks of yeast, as well as baking soda (bicarbonate of soda) and baking powder.  All the items needed to make some form of bread.  The latter two will allow you to make non-yeast bread like Soda Bread.  If you have an older relative that makes bread, but doesn't understand the internet help them out.  We're all in this together.  Where I live the low price bulk yeasts are all being sold out, but are popping up on Amazon and Ebay at 3x or more the price.  This is also THE time to start learning how to make Levain, as that needs time to be ready and may be the only form of yeast that may be available.  Good Luck and be safe.  I am sending love to all of you around the world.

snippet.textDisplay: other option would be adding the water drop per drop(takes you around 3minutes and u end up with a slightly drier dough but that also reduces the bakingtime which saves nutrients and if your into nutrients you should open the oven every few minutes for a fewseconds to help let the moisture escape. this reduces the baking time too)  if you cant or dont wanna use yeast use a knifetip of salt grinded  to powder and dont kneed(dont compress the dough at all) but fold it invery carefully(use dont even need to let the dough rest longer using this technique. 1 hour should be enough i guess. it makes a huge difference in flavor and it raises a little better. i really wanna add is that yeast reduces the protein content of the dough since it digests a part of it. the reason people use yeast is because its easier to digest this way but you obviously have to eat more/more frequently to reach your desired protein intake^^ and yea i guess that why many cultures enjoy flatbreads they are done quickly and u lose the least nutrients. greetings haha thought id wright something usefull today ^^ last thing i wanna mention is that if you never tried it eat raw dough(meaning only water flour..and salt to taste and see how little you now need to feel "full" and nurished

snippet.textDisplay:
I just made banana oatmeal muffins. No flour required,
3 cups oatmeal
3 almost brown banana, smash into paste
1 tea spoon cinnamon
2 tea spoon baking powder
Pinch of nutmeg powder
1/2 tea spoon salt
2 eggs
1 +1/2 cup of milk
2 table spoon of chocolate chips or raisins/walnuts
Beat eggs with smesh banana, +milk
Combine all dry ingredients into the wet ingredients, put into muffins pan or cake pan, bake for 25 minutes
No sugar needed, the banana provides the natural sugar, chocolate chips are already sweet
snippet.textOriginal:
I just made banana oatmeal muffins.  No flour required,
3 cups oatmeal 
3 almost brown banana, smash into paste 
1 tea spoon cinnamon 
2 tea spoon baking powder 
Pinch of nutmeg powder 
1/2 tea spoon salt 
2 eggs 
1 +1/2 cup of milk
2 table spoon of chocolate chips or raisins/walnuts 
Beat eggs with smesh banana, +milk
Combine all dry ingredients into the wet ingredients,  put  into muffins pan or cake pan, bake for 25 minutes 
No sugar needed, the banana provides the natural sugar, chocolate chips are already sweet
